Reposted from @metopera Experience one of America’s greatest operas with this weekend’s free two-day presentation of the Gershwins’ Porgy and Bess. Last season’s historic new production stars bass-baritone @ericowensopera and soprano @angeljoyblue in the title roles, alongside sopranos @goldsoprano and Latonia Moore, mezzo-soprano Denyce Graves (@gravesmontgomery), tenor @myfreddieballentine, and bass-baritones Alfred Walker and @donovansingletary. @conductordavidrobertson leads the powerful performance, available tonight, September 4, beginning at 7:30PM ET until Sunday, September 6, at 6:30PM ET.

Access the stream, with subtitles, via the link in our story or through the Met Opera on Demand apps for Apple, Amazon, and Roku devices and Samsung Smart TV. The free streams are available on the apps without logging in by clicking “Browse and Preview” in the apps for connected TV, and “Explore the App” on tablets and mobile devices.

